### Diplomatic Posts

Kenneth Rogoff's impactful tenure as [Chief Economist of the International Monetary Fund](/Chief_Economist_of_the_International_Monetary_Fund) from 2001 to 2003 saw him at the forefront of global economic policy. He took on this critical role following [Michael Mussa](/Michael_Mussa) and subsequently passed the torch to [Raghuram Rajan](/Raghuram_Rajan), leaving an indelible mark on the institution and the international financial landscape.